&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6444&quot; title=&quot;HttpPartitionTest uses real-time get to verify docs exist in replicas which gets routed to an active replica so is not actually verifying the replica recovered correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-6444&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-6444&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Use distrib=false to ensure real-time get request only hits the replica we&apos;re testing for proper recovery.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14114257" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 20:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmmm, when did real-time get start being routed to a leader automatically?  Any replica should do for most common usecases.  Or did it get routed to the leader because the replica being queried was not active?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14114333" author="thelabdude" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 20:55:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, bad description. The /get&apos;s were hitting the leader because the replica was not active - will fix the description of this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
